its%20independence%2C%20a%20violent%20quest%20that%20has%20bred%20generations%20of%20Ukrainians%20who%20time%20and%20time%20again%20are%20forced%20to%20choose%20between%20survival%20and%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHer%20tale%20dates%20back%20to%20the%20late%201920s%2C%20when%20Soviet%20authorities%20stripped%20Lihusha's%20ancestors%20of%20their%20land%20in%20the%20eastern%20Donbas%20region%20and%20forced%20them%20onto%20a%20collective%20farm%2C%20according%20to%20The%20Journal.%20In%20the%20following%20years%2C%20the%20Soviets%20would%20seek%20Ukrainian%20grain%20to%20sell%20abroad%20in%20a%20plot%20that%20ultimately%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukrainian-president-zelenskyy-compares-russian-invasion-war-stalin-era-genocide-2022-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresulted%20in%20widespread%20famine%20and%20millions%20of%20deaths%20across%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20time%20Lihusha%20fled%20Russian%20invaders%20was%20as%20a%20baby%20in%20her%20mother's%20arms%20in%201932%2C%20the%20Journal%20reported.%20Her%20family%20left%20their%20home%20in%20an%20eastern%20Ukrainian%20village%20for%20the%20nearby%20city%20of%20Horlivka%20after%20Soviet%20authorities%20took%20control%20of%20the%20village's%20grain%20supply.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20her%20relatives%20who%20stayed%20behind%20would%20later%20die%20of%20hunger%2C%20Lihusha%20and%20her%20daughter%20told%20the%20outlet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20World%20War%20II%2C%20Lihusha%20and%20her%20family%20returned%20home%20to%20their%20village.%20But%20in%20the%20post-war%20years%2C%20Ukraine%20was%20hit%20by%20a%20wave%20of%20Russification%20that%20led%20to%20a%20dwindling%20Ukrainian%20culture%20in%20the%20country%2C%20the%20Journal%20reported.%20Lihusha%20taught%20Ukrainian%20language%20and%20literature%20in%20the%20village.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Ukraine%20held%20a%20referendum%20for%20independence%20from%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20in%201991%2C%20Lihusha's%20daughter%2C%20Valentyna%20Pryshchepa%2C%20told%20the%20Journal%20that%20she%20convinced%20all%20her%20family%20members%20to%20vote%20yes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELihusha's%20family%20bought%20her%20a%20house%20near%20Kyiv%20in%202004%20where%20she%20lived%20until%20Russian%20troops%20invaded%20last%20year.%20Once%20again%2C%20she%20was%20forced%20to%20flee%20her%20home.%20Lihusha%20and%20her%20daughter%20went%20to%20Poland%2C%20they%20told%20the%20Journal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20village%20from%20which%20she%20first%20fled%20as%20a%20baby%20is%20now%20near%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-front-line-forces-fighting-through-russia-surovikin-line-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efrontlines%20of%20fighting%20in%20the%20Donbas%20area%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20according%20to%20the%20outlet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20have%20nothing%20left%20here%2C%20only%20my%20memories%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20the%20Journal%20in%20a%20spring%202022%20interview.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELihusha%20died%20a%20year%20later%20of%20kidney%20disease.%20She%20is%20buried%20next%20to%20her%20husband%20in%20a%20cemetery%20near%20Kyiv%2C%20the%20outlet%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukrainian-woman-fled-russia-cursed-putins-bastards-2023-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694223686000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64fbc4323d392300197774f0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukrainian-woman-fled-russia-cursed-putins-bastards-2023-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Kateryna%20Lihusha%2C%20who%20died%20this%20year%20in%20Poland%2C%20first%20fled%20her%20homeland%2090%20years%20ago.%20Her%20story%20exemplifies%20Russia's%20centuries-long%20aim%20to%20control%20Ukraine.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22esnodgrass%40insider.com%20(Erin%20Snodgrass)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A34%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22