20the%20art%20look%203D%2C%20which%20helped%20the%20archeologists%20make%20their%20new%20discovery.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EArchaeologists%20have%20discovered%20new%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhunting-scene-cave-painting-is-oldest-story-in-pictures-2019-12%5C%22%3EPaleolithic%20animal%20paintings%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20years%20ago%20hidden%20in%20a%20cave%20using%20an%20updated%20photography%20technique.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20over%20700%20paintings%20lining%20the%20rock%20walls%20of%20the%20Cave%20of%20La%20Pasiega%20in%20north-central%20Spain%2C%20which%20anthropologists%20first%20discovered%20in%201911.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20most%20part%2C%20scientists%20viewed%20them%20as%20two-dimensional%20drawings.%20But%20the%20ancient%20artists%20actually%20incorporated%20bumps%2C%20dips%2C%20and%20crevices%20from%20the%20rocks%20into%20their%20art%20that%20can't%20be%20fully%20appreciated%20in%202D.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20why%20a%20team%20of%20researchers%20recently%20used%20a%20technique%20called%20stereoscopic%20photography%20to%20observe%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fneanderthal-oldest-cave-drawings-found-france-2023-6%5C%22%3Ecave%20art%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20a%20unique%20new%20way.%20They%20published%20their%20results%20in%20the%20journal%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.15184%2Faqy.2023.122%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAntiquity%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20August.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStereoscopic%20photography%20is%20a%20technique%20that%20uses%20two%20separate%20images%20to%20give%20the%20illusion%20of%203D.%3Cstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20artists%20played%20with%20the%20lights%20and%20shadows%20produced%20by%20the%20volumes%20of%20the%20cave%20walls%2C%26quot%3B%20archaeologist%20Raquel%20Asiain%2C%20lead%20author%20on%20the%20paper%2C%20told%20Insider%20via%20email.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20crack%20in%20the%20wall%20might%20define%20the%20horse's%20chest%2C%20for%20example.%20Tracings%20or%20sketches%20might%20miss%20nuances%20in%20the%20rocks%20that%203D%20images%20can%20bring%20to%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EAn%20old%20technique%20reveals%20new%20details%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDating%20back%20to%20the%201800s%2C%20stereoscopic%20photography%20itself%20is%20not%20new.%20Perhaps%20its%20most%20recognizable%20use%20is%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple-is-selling-the-view-master-virtual-reality-headset-2016-2%5C%22%3EView-Masters%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20the%20children's%20toy%20that%20presents%20separate%20images%20to%20the%20left%20and%20right%20eyes%2C%20creating%20a%203D%20illusion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAsiain%20and%20her%20co-authors%20used%20a%20similar%20technique%2C%20taking%20two%20images%202.5%20inches%20apart%20to%20mimic%20the%20average%20distance%20between%20the%20pupils%20of%20human%20eyes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUsing%20software%2C%20including%20Photoshop%20and%20DStretch%2C%20they%20processed%20the%20images%20for%203D%20glasses%20or%20virtual%20reality%20devices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20the%20scientists%20were%20able%20to%20see%20the%20drawings%20in%203D%2C%20they%20saw%20three%20new%20figures%20among%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.flickr.com%2Fphotos%2F196948634%40N08%2Falbums%2F72177720303548371%2Fwith%2F52488916319%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecave's%20walls%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20had%20never%20been%20seen%20before.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20figures%20included%20two%20horses%20and%20an%20extinct%20cattle%20species%20called%20an%20aurochs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThose%20figures%20were%20always%20there%2C%20but%20possibly%20the%20way%20of%20studying%20them%20kept%20them%20hidden%2C%26quot%3B%20Asiain%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221421%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Four%20images%20of%20a%20Paleolithic%20cave%20drawing%20of%20an%20auroch%20in%