20calculation%20method%20often%20begins%20by%20loading%20the%20software%20with%20external%20data%20on%20unit-conversion%20factors%20or%20emission%20factors%20and%20their%20potential%20impact%20on%20the%20climate.%20This%20information%20is%20usually%20found%20on%20open%20databases%20of%20national%20agencies%20such%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.epa.gov%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUS%20Environmental%20Protection%20Agency%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20international%20databases%20like%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.iea.org%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EInternational%20Energy%20Agency%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Startups%20including%20Sinai%2C%20Carbon%20Analytics%2C%20and%20Watershed%20base%20their%20accounting%20on%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fghgprotocol.org%2Fstandards%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGreenhouse%20Gas%20Protocol%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20global%20standard%20that%20provides%20a%20framework%20for%20measuring%20the%20emissions%20of%20corporations%2C%20cities%2C%20and%20other%20sectors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Headshot%20of%20Alissa%20Benchimol%2C%20who%20is%20wearing%20a%20black%20blouse%20and%20black%20glasses%20against%20the%20backdrop%20of%20a%20tree%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64f7749f1b7ced0019c86f7a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222274%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAlissa%20Benchimol%2C%20the%20senior%20program%20officer%20at%20the%20Greenhouse%20Gas%20Management%20Institute.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Alissa%20Benchimol%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3EFunctionalities%20are%20added%20to%20the%20software%20to%20create%20the%20company%20%26quot%3Bprofile%26quot%3B%20by%20%26quot%3Bdocumenting%20their%20operation%20processes%2C%20identifying%20unique%20emission%20sources%2C%20and%20enabling%20year-to-year%20data%20storage%20and%20calculations%2C%26quot%3B%20Benchimol%20said.%3Cp%3EWatershed%20software%2C%20for%20example%2C%20calculates%20a%20company's%20carbon%20footprint%20based%20on%20financial%20data%20that's%20uploaded%20to%20the%20platform.%20The%20data%20includes%20all%20operating%20costs%2C%20including%2C%20for%20example%2C%20employees'%20flights.%20The%20miles%20flown%20and%20the%20money%20spent%20are%20loaded%20into%20the%20system%2C%20which%20then%20comes%20up%20with%20the%20emission%20figures.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20startups%20are%20helping%20companies%20track%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.workforclimate.org%2Fpost%2Fwhats-the-difference-scope-1-2-and-3-corporate-emissions%3Fgclid%3DCj0KCQjwi7GnBhDXARIsAFLvH4lcBAYQfFfRDWozKBPJZmPl2e7AUkN2_bIE1tgZaac9k4Gqu4BevFQaArMGEALw_wcB%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethree%20scope%20emissions%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20scope%201%2C%20which%20covers%20emissions%20from%20sources%20that%20a%20company%20owns%20or%20controls%20directly%3B%20scope%202%2C%20which%20are%20emissions%20from%20purchased%20energy%20that%20a%20company%20indirectly%20causes%3B%20and%20scope%203%2C%20which%20are%20all%20other%20indirect%20emissions%20that%20occur%20across%20the%20value%20chain%20and%20are%20outside%20of%20a%20business's%20control%2C%20such%20as%20how%20much%20electricity%20a%20supplier%20uses%20or%20the%20carbon%20footprint%20of%20delivering%20the%20products%20to%20consumers.%20But%20it's%20challenging%20to%20precisely%20monitor%20this%20since%20companies'%20emissions%20are%20not%20the%20same%2C%20and%20they%20often%20overlap.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20companies%20will%20soon%20have%20no%20choice%20in%20reporting%20their%20carbon%20emissions.%20Last%20year%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sec.gov%2Fnews%2Fpress-release%2F2022-46%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESecurities%20and%20Exchange%20Commission%3C%2Fa%3E%20released%20a%20proposal%20that%20would%20require%20publicly%20traded%20companies%20to%20disclose%20all%20their%20emission%20scopes%2C%20including%20scope%203%2C%20the%20most%20difficult%20to%20track.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20many%20companies%20are%20sharing%20this%20data%20already%2C%20not%20all%20of%20them%20have%20been%20inspired%20to%20take%20action.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20nearly%2020%2C000%20organizations%20voluntarily%20released%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-nonprofit-cdp-holds-companies-accountable-sustainability-goals-2022-4%5C%22%3Eenvironmental%20information%20through%20CDP%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20nonprofit%20that%20has%20run%20a%20global%20disclosure%20system%20for%20carbon%20emissions%20for%20over%20two%20decades.%20The%20number%20represents%20over%2080%25%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.investopedia.com%2Fterms%2Ff%2Ffootsie.asp%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFTSE%20100%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-the-sp-500%5C%22%3ES%26amp%3BP%20500%20index%20companies%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20companies%20actually%20do%20know%20what%20their%20emissions%20look%20like%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Lauren%20Gifford%2C%20the%20associate%20director%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.soilcarbonsolutionscenter.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESoil%20Carbon%20Solutions%20Center%20at%20Colorado%20State%20University%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20studies%20carbon%20markets%2C%20climate%20finance%2C%20and%20climate%20tech.%20Gifford%20said%20most%20of%20the%20startups%20are%20taking%20the%20labor%20off%20companies%20to%20track%20their%20emissions%2C%20%26quot%3Bbut%20having%20the%20capacity%20to%20respond%20to%20that%20is%20another%20conversation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20promise%20of%20data-driven%20sustainability%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECarbon-accounting%20startups%20say%20that%20tracking%20is%20just%20the%20first%20of%20several%20steps.%20Once%20the%20company%20has%20its%20data%2C%20it%20needs%20to%20implement%20changes%2C%20and%20that's%20where%20technology%20plays%20a%20crucial%20role.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWatershed%20uses%20the%20data%20it%20collects%20to%20recommend%20decarbonization%20solutions%2C%20such%20as%20clean%20energy%20and%20carbon-removal%20projects%2C%20to%20companies.%20Case%20in%20point%3A%20It's%20helping%20DoorDash%20develop%20pilot%20programs%2C%20including%20an%20initiative%20to%20use%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdasher.doordash.com%2Fen-us%2Fabout%2Felectric-vehicles%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eelectric%20vehicles%20to%20reduce%20emissions%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20its%20deliveries.%20The%20software%20also%20creates%20disclosure%20reports%2C%20which%20require%20the%20company%20to%20answer%20a%20series%20of%20questions%20that%20will%20be%20used%20to%20score%20its%20environmental%20progress.%20These%20reports%20can%20then%20be%20shared%20with%20CDP.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222614%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Screenshot%20of%20Watershed's%20interface%20that%20shows%20a%20bar%20graph%20breakdown%20of%20a%20company's%20carbon%20emissions%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64f9dc758a78400019621644%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221779%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWatershed%20can%20provide%20a%20breakdown%20of%20a%20company's%20yearly%20carbon%20emissions.%3Cp%3EWatershed%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3EThe%20Sinai%20platform%20also%20suggests%20solutions%20based%20on%20a%20process%20of%20carbon%20pricing.%20Its%20software%20extrapolates%20a%20scenario%20where%20the%20company%20doesn't%20take%20steps%20to%20reduce%20its%20emissions%20and%20a%20second%20scenario%20where%20it%20does%20make%20changes%2C%20and%20then%20recommends%20mitigation%20measures%20and%20associated%20costs.%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20software%20all