pan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20collecting%20manuscripts%20from%20Jain%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ebhandaras%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Eacross%20Rajasthan%20and%20Gujarat%20are%20now%20well-documented.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndian%20manuscript%20heritage%20possesses%20a%20distinctive%20confluence%20of%20religious%20and%20state%20patronage%2C%20as%20well%20as%20mercantile%20and%20military%20scribal%20practices%2C%20leading%20to%20the%20emergence%20of%20a%20diverse%20scriptural%20ecology.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20example%2C%20traveling%20Buddhist%20monks%20and%20mendicants%20wrote%20in%20the%20prevalent%20local%20scripts%20they%20encountered%20in%20their%20journeys.%20In%20fact%2C%20the%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farchive.org%2Fdetails%2FLalitVistarEkSamikshatmakAdhyayanDr.Rambali%2Fpage%2Fn51%2Fmode%2F2up%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ELalit%20Vistar%20Sutra%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20Mahayana%20Buddhism%E2%80%99s%20key%20text%20composed%20in%20about%20the%20third%20century%20AD%2C%20stresses%20the%20importance%20of%20learning%2064%20scripts%20along%20with%20arithmetic%2C%20chemistry%2C%20philosophy%20and%20statistics.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhat%20is%20interesting%20to%20note%20is%20that%20the%20text%20emphasises%20learning%20multiple%20scripts%20as%20the%20basis%20of%20%E2%80%9Creal%E2%80%9D%20education%2C%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Elokanuvartan%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9D%2C%20that%20is%20education%20in%20people%E2%80%99s%20conduct.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20more%20recent%20history%2C%20the%20role%20of%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.co.in%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DleksAAAAYAAJ%26printsec%3Dfrontcover%26dq%3DContributions%2Btowards%2Ba%2Bhistory%2Bof%2BBiblical%2Btranslations%2Bin%2BIndia%26hl%3Den%26newbks%3D1%26newbks_redir%3D0%26sa%3DX%26redir_esc%3Dy%23v%3Donepage%26q%3DContributions%2520towards%2520a%2520history%2520of%2520Biblical%2520translations%2520in%2520India%26f%3Dfalse%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ECalcutta%20Auxiliary%20Bible%20Society%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.co.in%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DJLswmQEACAAJ%26dq%3DBaptist%2BMission%2Bkaithi%2Bbible%26hl%3Den%26newbks%3D1%26newbks_redir%3D0%26sa%3DX%26redir_esc%3Dy%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EBaptist%20Mission%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.co.in%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DqxUFAAAAQAAJ%26pg%3DPR89%26dq%3DBaptist%2BMission%2Bkaithi%2Bbible%26hl%3Den%26newbks%3D1%26newbks_redir%3D0%26sa%3DX%26ved%3D2ahUKEwjx2auxjv2AAxVawjgGHfjHCv4Q6AF6BAhiEAI%23v%3Donepage%26q%3DBaptist%2520Mission%2520kaithi%2520bible%26f%3Dfalse%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EBritish%20and%20Foreign%20Bible%20Society%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20publishing%20various%20religious%20texts%20in%20the%20Kaithi%20script%20is%20well-known.%20The%20recent%20assembling%20of%20the%20central%20Asian%20corpus%20of%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F26551682%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Efragmented%20Koran%20in%20the%20Bihari%20script%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20dating%20from%20the%20Sultanate%20period%20in%20India%20(13th%20to%2016th%20centuries)%2C%20also%20attests%20to%20the%20fluid%20script%20economy%20of%20pre-modern%20India.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESecular%20manuscript%20heritage%20was%20equally%20sustained%20by%20military%20and%20mercantile%20establishments.%20Sher%20Shah%20Suri%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Esanad%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20dated%20December%2015%2C%201640%2C%20chronicles%20the%20use%20of%20Kaithi%20for%20grant%20of%20passage%20to%20merchants%20and%20bankers.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bl.uk%2Fcollection-items%2Fthe-field-exercise-of-the-british-army%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Field%20Exercise%20of%20the%20British%20Army%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(1846)%20was%20proposed%20to%20be%20written%20in%20the%20Kaithi%20script.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EBal%20Dipak%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E(1886)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Ea%20new%20Hindi%20series%20by%20Sahib%20Prasad%20Sinha%20and%20introduced%20by%20Frederic%20Pincott%2C%20promoted%20Kaithi%20script-learning%20amongst%20new%20cadres%20of%20the%20Bihar%20Regiment.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20552px)%2085vw%2C%20552px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F08154003%2FKaithi-manuscript-II.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22552%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F08154003%2FKaithi-manuscript-II.png%20552w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F08154003%2FKaithi-manuscript-II-300x170.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-672130%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22313%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20manuscript%20written%20using%20Kaithi.%20Photo%3A%20Rajendra%20Prasad%20Pandey%2FScribd.%20CC%20BY-NC.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELangdi%20Hindi%2C%20a%20form%20of%20script%20used%20exclusively%20for%20bookkeeping%20in%20Haryana%20and%20the%20regions%20surrounding%20it%20remains%20completely%20undocumented.%20Mahajani%20was%20promoted%20by%20the%20colonial%20military%20and%20was%20widely%20used%20to%20record%20day-to-day%20transactions%20in%20various%20parts%20of%20western%20and%20northern%20India.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20number%20of%20scientific%20and%20poetic%20treatises%20from%20both%20Sanskritic%20and%20Persian%20traditions%20were%20written%20in%20Braj%20using%20the%20Gurumukhi%20script%20in%20the%20seventeenth%20and%20eighteenth-century%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farchive.org%2Fstream%2Fin.ernet.dli.2015.461302%2F2015.461302.A-History-Of-Indian-Literature-Vol8_djvu.txt%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EPunjab%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20the%20presence%20of%20multiple%20scripts%20reflects%20India%E2%80%99s%20dynamic%20manuscript%20past%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.namami.gov.in%2Fwhat-is-menuscript%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20manuscript%20policies%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20have%20underserved%20this%20bountiful%20heritage.%20It%20is%20critical%20to%20identify%20a%20home%20for%20documents%20that%20do%20not%20follow%20the%20manuscript%20canons%20as%20devised%20by%20orientalist%20assumptions%20of%20antiquity%2C%20historical%20eminence%20and%20scriptural%20consistency.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAdditionally%2C%20there%20is%20also%20the%20need%20to%20identify%20manuscripts%20as%20an%20assemblage%20of%20a%20variety%20of%20technologies%20and%20material%20relationships%20that%20requires%20one%20to%20go%20beyond%20the%20content-centric%20view%20of%20manuscripts.%20This%20could%20only%20be%20achieved%20if%20regional%20manuscript%20centres%20are%20also%20strengthened%20to%20promote%20local%20histories%20of%20scribal%20practices%20and%20preservation.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThus%2C%20it%20is%20equally%20important%20to%20acknowledge%20the%20role%20of%20various%20communities%20in%20the%20preservation%20and%20promotion%20of%20manuscripts.%20In%20this%20regard%2C%20the%20contributions%20of%20different%20castes%20of%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20in%20maintaining%20manuscripts%20needs%20special%20mention.%20As%20documented%20by%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianculture.gov.in%2Frarebooks%2Fcastes-and-tribes-southern-india-vol-iv-k-m%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ehistorians%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20of%20the%20region%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ehakku%20patras%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20the%20patronage%20documents%20maintained%20by%20various%20%E2%80%9Cmendicant%20communities%E2%80%9D%2C%20were%20critical%20sources%20of%20understanding%20the%20caste%20dynamics%20of%20the%20region.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.co.in%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DogluAAAAMAAJ%26q%3Darchaeology%2Bas%2Bhistory%2Bin%2Bearly%2Bsouth%2Basia%26dq%3Darchaeology%2Bas%2Bhistory%2Bin%2Bearly%2Bsouth%2Basia%26hl%3Den%26newbks%3D1%26newbks_redir%3D0%26sa%3DX%26redir_esc%3Dy%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EOdia%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Epothis%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ELaxmipurana%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EBrij%20Bihar%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ESri%20Ramalilamruta%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20have%20been%20copied%20and%20maintained%20by%20various%20non-%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Esavarna%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20castes%20such%20as%20barbers%2C%20potters%20and%20washermen.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ERamchandra%20Vihara%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20a%20manuscript%20from%20early%20modern%20Odisha%2C%20was%20transcribed%20by%20a%20Muslim%2C%20Naseeb%20Khan.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20another%20important%20contribution%20of%20different%20castes%20to%20the%20scribal%20ecology%20of%20India%20was%20in%20developing%20writing%20instruments%20made%20of%20ivory%2C%20bone%20or%20reed%2C%20as%20well%20as%20developing%20various%20kinds%20of%20preservation%20processes%20using%20chemical%20and%20fumigation%20techniques%2C%20specialised%20inks%20and%20clothes.%20The%20preparation%20of%20traditional%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Edummala%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Eoil%20and%20neem%20wood%20special%20cupboards%20used%20in%20southern%20India%20are%20some%20of%20the%20methods%20of%20palm-leaf%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.ifla.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Ffiles%2Fassets%2Fpac%2FDocuments%2Fpac_sri_lanka_report_best_practices_for_conservation_of_palm-leaf_manuscripts_.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Econservation%20practices%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20involved%20various%20communities.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fculture%2Fbharati-intermediary-script-iit-madras-indian-languages-unicode%5C%22%3EWhy%20It%20Isn%E2%80%99t%20Easy%20to%20Devise%20an%20Intermediary%20Script%20for%20Indian%20Languages%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERecent%20manuscript%20and%20archival%20collections%20across%20many%20parts%20of%20the%20world%20acknowledge%20the%20communitarian%20contexts%20of%20manuscripts.%20The%20mobilisation%20of%20local%20communities%20in%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftombouctoumanuscripts.uct.ac.za%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Epreservation%20of%20Timbuktu%20manuscripts%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20is%20widely%20recognised.%20Similarly%2C%20Nepal%E2%80%99s%20community%20manuscript%20project%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farchive.org%2Fdetails%2Fasha-saphookuthiya-saphoo-dhalah-a-short-catalogue-of-asha-archives-edited-by-raja-shakya%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EAsa%20Archives%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20could%20also%20serve%20as%20an%20interesting%20model%20for%20creating%20a%20more%20capacious%20and%20accessible%20manuscript%20collection.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIf%20these%20complex%20heritage%20practices%20need%20attention%2C%20it%20would%20also%20assist%20the%20cause%20of%20manuscript%20curation%20in%20India%20to%20substantiate%20the%20international%20context%20of%20the%20production%20of%20various%20manuscript%20collections.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdreamsea.co%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EDREAMSEA%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20a%20collaboration%20between%20Indonesia%2C%20Thailand%20and%20Laos%2C%20has%20made%20available%20a%20number%20of%20endangered%20repositories%20that%20recount%20the%20fascinating%20international%20provenance%20of%20various%20manuscripts%20from%20the%20region%2C%20including%20some%20from%20India.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhmml.org%2Fstories%2Fseries-books-syriac-manuscripts-in-india%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ESpecialised%20manuscript%20collections%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20containing%20rare%2C%20banned%20books%20reproduced%20in%20Syriac%2C%20Malayalam%2C%20and%20Malayalam%20Garshuni%20by%20Christian%20priests%20in%20early%20modern%20India%20would%20benefit%20immensely%20from%20international%20contextualisation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESimilarly%2C%20research%20conducted%20by%20Russian%20Indologists%2C%20such%20as%20K.G.%20Maximov%E2%80%99s%20study%20of%20Buddhist%20heritage%20in%20southern%20Turkmenistan%20and%20Ajanta%20and%20Ellora%20sculptures%2C%20require%20international%20scholarly%20collaboration.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20recently%20held%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2FPressReleasePage.aspx%3FPRID%3D1940832%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EFestival%20of%20Libraries%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20concluded%20with%20a%20memorandum%20of%20understanding%20between%20three%20prominent%20libraries%20in%20India%20for%20rare%20manuscript%20sharing%20and%20digitisation.%20While%20this%20is%20a%20step%20ahead%2C%20the%20need%20for%20today%E2%80%99s%20research%20is%20not%20just%20digital%20reproduction%20of%20manuscripts%2C%20but%20providing%20nuanced%2C%20localised%20metadata%20for%20them.%20More%20importantly%2C%20there%20is%20also%20the%20need%20to%20reconfigure%20the%20%E2%80%98rarity%E2%80%99%20of%20manuscripts%20beyond%20specific%20scripts%20and%20their%20institutional%20associations.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAn%20inclusive%20and%20dynamic%20vision%20of%20manuscripts