percent%20of%20the%20power%20needs%20of%20the%20house.%20Additionally%2C%20we%20also%20have%20a%20rainwater%20harvesting%20plant%20set%20up.%20We%20catch%20about%2030%2C000%20litres%20of%20water%20in%20our%20underground%20water%20storage%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20house%20also%20believes%20in%20zero%20waste%20and%20has%20a%20water%20filtration%20system.%20%E2%80%9CAll%20our%20grey%20water%20(the%20dirty%20but%20reusable%20water%20from%20sinks%2C%20washing%20machines)%20is%20filtered%20and%20is%20used%20in%20cleaning%20and%20drinking.%20Even%20the%20wood%20packaging%20in%20which%20our%20windows%20and%20doors%20came%20were%20used%20to%20make%20some%20sort%20of%20furniture%20so%20that%20nothing%20goes%20to%20waste%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20house%20also%20has%20double%20glazing%20in%20the%20windows%20to%20keep%20it%20warm%20during%20the%20winter.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20their%20effort%20to%20combine%20traditional%20and%20contemporary%20elements%20in%20their%20home%2C%20the%20Budhrajas%20acquired%20all%20of%20their%20wood%20from%20a%20%3Cem%3Ekabadiya%C2%A0%20%3C%2Fem%3E(scrap%20dealer)%20who%20sources%20the%20wood%20from%20dismantled%20and%20ageing%20government%20and%20residential%20structures%20in%20Himachal%20Pradesh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20believe%20in%20reusing%20and%20upcycling.%20The%20wood%20in%20some%20of%20our%20doors%20is%20nearly%20100%20years%20old%2C%E2%80%9D%20informs%20Anuradha.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20also%20used%20the%20Himalayan%20Black%20State%2C%20a%20type%20of%20tile%20local%20to%20the%20state%2C%20for%20the%20flooring%20and%20cladding%20of%20the%20house.%20It%20is%20a%20great%20conductor%20of%20heat.%20We%20also%20use%20electrical%20heating%20using%20solar%20power%20to%20keep%20the%20house%20warm%20for%20the%20harsh%20winters%2C%E2%80%9D%20adds%20Anuradha.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20data-instgrm-version%3D%5C%2214%5C%22%20data-instgrm-permalink%3D